title: Girls Cross Country Roundup: Plymouth finishes fourth
text:
Girls Cross Country Roundup: Plymouth finishes fourth Staff report 4:28 p.m. EDT October 3, 2015 STK Stock CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Buckeye Central Invitational 
Northmor was first at the Buckeye Central Invitational (44 points), led by Kristen Duryea (2nd, 19:50), Isabelle Ditullio (4th, 20:12), Samantha Peters (6th, 20:38), Brooke Bennett (15th, 21:18) and Sydney Jennete (17th, 21:28). 
Colonel Crawford was second (100 points), led by Anna Reffey (5th, 20:27), Emily Eimper(13th, 21:11), Courtney Britt (16th, 21:19), Haley Laughbaum (28th, 22:59) and Alyssa Spears (38th, 23:39). 
Plymouth was fourth at the Buckeye Central Invitational (119 points), led by Jessica Porter (11th, 20:59), Kendall Sanders (20th, 21:51), Mattie Lunceford (27th, 22:45), Claudia Caudill (30th, 23:06) and Gracie Roberts (35th, 23:19). 
Highland was fifth (134 points), led by Sophia Thompson (7th, 20:44), Laura Spearman (12th, 21:10), Jena Buchholz (25th, 22:19), Olivia Longhenry (46th, 23:49) and Elizabeth Jensen (50th, 23:54). 
Mansfield Christian was seventh (153 points), led by Clare Reynolds (1st, 19:15), Abby Reynolds (18th, 21:33), Maggio Myers (32nd, 23:08), Rebecca Huff (45th, 23:47) and Allisyaa Atkenson (77th, 26:20). 
Buckeye Central was tenth (264 points), led by Tamara Metzger (34th, 23:29), Kendra Stahl(46th, 23:53), Zoe Rutledge (57th, 25:22), Haley Kalb (63rd, 26:36) and Jordyn Kaple(64th, 26:37). 
Wynford was eleventh (283 points), led by Morgan Beaschler (44th, 23:50), Katherine Hall (53rd, 24:19), Hannah Weithman (58th, 25:33), Annie Fienning (59th, 25:33) and Alexa Oberlander (69th, 30:11). 
Crestline was led by Caitlyn (31st, 23:07) and Summer Mowry (91st, 28:00). 
Vannessa Grant (96th, 29:00) was the only runner for Lucas. 
Vermilion Invitational 
Perkins placed first (67 points) out of 16 teams on Saturday. 
Willard was led by ninth place finisher Emily Rothhaar in 21:24 Saturday at the Vermilion Invitational. Rothhaarâ€™s teammates Lesley Burton (47th, 23:02), Alyssa Strayer (57th, 23:24), Felicia Rosvanis (62nd, 23:40) and Taylor Chaffins (76th, 24:31) helped the team to a eleventh place finish with 251 points. 
Pickerington Panther Invitational 
Shaker Heights placed first (84 points) out of 33 teams on Saturday. 
Fredericktown placed eighth (253 points), led by Rachel Tumbleson (22nd, 20:29), Rachel Caputo (51st, 21:14), Nichole Groseclose (53rd, 21:17), Lauren Dais (55th, 21:20) and Emily Cobb (72nd, 21:40). 
Cardington placed thirty-first (918 points), led by Alicia McElwee (163rd, 23:26), Abby Lorimer (220th 25:01), Sage Brannon (225 25:18), Bailey Shafer (226th, 25:21) and Jessica Shoor (244, 26:29). 
North Union Invitational 
Mount Gilead was first at the North Union Invitational (55 points), led by Jenna Shipman (2nd, 20:15), Hannah Bush (6th, 20:54), Darcy Picker (8th, 21:15), Kelsey Snyder (18th, 22:08) and Micah James (23rd, 22:29). 
Bucyrus was second (90 points), led by Julia VanVoorhis (9th, )21:42, Mirium Everett (10th, 21:49), Shaylee Campbell (12th, 21:53), Desiree Sigler (27th, 22:52), and Jessica Campbell (32, 23:22). 
Galion was sixth (141 points), led by Megan Zeir (16th, ) 22:05, Ashlie Sallee (18th, 22:09), Sari Conner (25th, 22:48), Lauren Huggins (40th, 24:16) and Kelsey Hoffman (42nd, 24:44). Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RnoUms More Stories
